{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb9640d65-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201/s1416/c/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201, § 1416(c)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of the chapter 133B of this title that relates to terrorism by adding this section, was executed by adding this section to this chapter to reflect the probable intent of Congress. This title does not contain a chapter 133B."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb9640d66-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2001—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/56"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–56","children":[],"tail":" substituted “2332a of this title” for “2332c of this title” and struck out “chemical” before “weapon of”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/294"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–294","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2332d"},"text":"section 2332d of this title","children":[],"tail":", relating to requests for military assistance to enforce prohibition in certain emergencies, as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
